  "planContent": "# 🏗️ Architecture Blueprint\n\n## App Overview\nA client-side PDF document manipulation tool that allows users to upload a PDF, visualize its pages as image thumbnails, select specific ranges or individual pages for extraction, and download the resulting sub-document without ever uploading data to a server.\n\n## Core Features\n- Local File Upload: File input restricted to `.pdf` format.\n- Page Previews: Render PDF pages as high-fidelity thumbnails using PDF.js.\n- Page Selection: Click-to-toggle selection for individual pages.\n- Range Extraction: Input field for specific page ranges (e.g., \"1-3, 5\").\n- Bulk Actions: Select All, Deselect All, and Invert Selection buttons.\n- PDF Generation: Re-construct a new PDF document from selected pages.\n- Dark Mode Interface: Full dark-themed UI with high-contrast accessibility.\n\n## UI & Layout Strategy\n- **Layout type**: Single-column vertical stack with a fixed header and responsive grid for thumbnails.\n- **Header**: Contains App Title (\"FORGE PDF Splitter\"), Upload File button (custom-styled), and a \"Download Selection\" button (disabled until selection exists).\n- **Main content area**: A scrollable canvas area displaying a grid of thumbnail cards. Each card contains a thumbnail image, page number label, and a selection checkbox.\n- **Controls**: Sticky control bar below the header containing Page Range Input, Select All/None buttons, and current page count indicators.\n- **Footer**: \"FORGE | Local-First PDF Utility | No data leaves your machine\"\n- **Color scheme**: FORGE dark theme (--bg:#0a0a0a, --surface:#171717, --accent:#3b82f6, --text:#e5e5e5, --border:#262626).\n- **Typography**: Inter (sans-serif).\n- **Responsive strategy**: Thumbnails grid switches from 4-col (desktop) to 2-col (tablet) to 1-col (mobile).\n- **Animations**: Subtle scale-up transition on card hover and fade-in for thumbnails once rendered.\n\n## Data Model & State\n| Variable | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| pdfDoc | Object | null | The loaded PDFDocumentProxy object. |\n| pages | Array | [] | Array of objects: { pageNumber: number, dataUrl: string, selected: boolean }. |\n| fileName | String | \"\" | Name of the original uploaded file. |\n| isProcessing | Boolean | false | Flag to disable UI interactions during heavy rendering. |\n\n- **localStorage key**: N/A (State is ephemeral for security and privacy; session-based only).\n- **Persistence strategy**: None; pages are cleared on refresh to ensure privacy.\n\n## Technical Stack & Libraries\n- **Required CDNs**: \n    - https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/3.11.174/pdf.min.js\n    - https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf-lib/1.17.1/pdf-lib.min.js\n- **Allowed**: PDF.js (rendering), PDF-lib (manipulation)\n- **APIs**: FileSystem Access API (for triggerring download)\n\n## Implementation Steps\n1. Setup document skeleton with FORGE dark CSS variables.\n2. Initialize PDF.js worker via CDN.\n3. Implement file input listener to capture `File` object.\n4. Use PDF.js to load the document and loop through pages.\n5. Convert each page to a data URL (canvas rendering) to display in the thumbnail grid.\n6. Create an state array `pages` tracking `pageNumber` and `selected` boolean.\n7. Implement event listener for thumbnail clicks to toggle `selected` state and CSS border styling.\n8. Build a parser for the \"Range Input\" string that updates the `selected` boolean in the `pages` array.\n9. Implement \"Select All/None/Invert\" functions to update DOM classes and state.\n10. Integrate `pdf-lib` to copy selected pages into a new `PDFDocument`.\n11. Implement trigger to download the generated Uint8Array as a blob.\n12. Add global loading spinner logic for `isProcessing` state.\n\n## Edge Cases & Error Handling\n- **Invalid PDF**: Catch Promise rejection from `pdfjsLib.getDocument()` and display a toast alert \"Invalid PDF file\".\n- **Empty State**: Show a prominent \"Drop PDF here\" overlay when no file is loaded.\n- **Large Files**: Implement `isProcessing` flag to prevent concurrent render calls.\n- **Selection Logic**: Ensure ranges like \"1-10\" are validated against actual total page count; truncate if input exceeds page count.\n- **Memory**: Clear individual `dataUrl` strings from memory if needed for extremely large PDF uploads.",
  "currentHTML": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no\">\n    <title>FORGE PDF Splitter</title>\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/3.11.174/pdf.min.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf-lib/1.17.1/pdf-lib.min.js\"></script>\n    <style>\n        :root {\n            --bg:#0a0a0a; --s1:#111111; --s2:#1a1a1a; --s3:#242424; --border:#1e293b;\n            --text:#f1f5f9; --muted:#64748b; --accent:#3b82f6; --accent-h:#2563eb;\n            --danger:#ef4444; --success:#22c55e; --warning:#f59e0b;\n        }\n        * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; }\n        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 40px; touch-action: manipulation; }\n        header { background: var(--s1); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 1rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; }\n        .controls { background: var(--s2); padding: 1rem; display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); flex-wrap: wrap; }\n        .btn { background: var(--s3); color: var(--text); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0.6rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; transition: 150ms; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; user-select: none; }\n        .btn:hover { background: var(--border); }\n        .btn-accent { background: var(--accent); border: none; }\n        .btn-accent:hover { background: var(--accent-h); }\n        .btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }\n        #grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; padding: 1rem; }\n        .card { background: var(--s1); border: 2px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; transition: 150ms; }\n        .card.selected { border-color: var(--accent); background: var(--s2); }\n        .card img { width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 4px; display: block; pointer-events: none; }\n        .card p { margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 11px; text-align: center; color: var(--muted); pointer-events: none; }\n        #dropzone { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; height: 50vh; border: 2px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; padding: 2rem; text-align: center; user-select: none; }\n        #dropzone:hover { border-color: var(--accent); background: var(--s1); }\n        input[type=\"text\"] { background: var(--s1); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text); padding: 0.6rem; border-radius: 4px; width: 100%; max-width: 150px; }\n        .hidden { display: none !important; }\n        .loader { position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.85); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; z-index: 1000; color: white; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<header>\n    <h1 style=\"font-size: 1.1rem;\">FORGE <span style=\"color:var(--muted)\">Splitter</span></h1>\n    <div>\n        <input type=\"file\" id=\"fileInput\" class=\"hidden\" accept=\"application/pdf\">\n        <button class=\"btn btn-accent\" id=\"downloadBtn\" onclick=\"processDownload()\" disabled>Export PDF</button>\n    </div>\n</header>\n\n<div class=\"controls\" id=\"controls\" style=\"display: none;\">\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"rangeInput\" placeholder=\"e.g. 1-3, 5\" onchange=\"applyRange()\">\n    <button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"toggleSelection('all')\">All</button>\n    <button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"toggleSelection('none')\">None</button>\n    <button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"toggleSelection('invert')\">Invert</button>\n    <span id=\"pageCount\" style=\"font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted);\"></span>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"dropzone\">\n    <p style=\"pointer-events:none\">Tap here or drop PDF file to start</p>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"grid\"></div>\n<div id=\"loader\" class=\"loader hidden\">Processing...</div>\n\n<footer style=\"text-align:center;padding:16px;color:var(--muted);font-size:12px;opacity:0.8;display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:center;gap:6px\"><span>Built with</span> <img src=\"https://forge-app-peach.vercel.app/logo.png\" alt=\"Forge\" style=\"width:14px;height:14px;border-radius:3px;object-fit:cover;\"> <a href=\"https://forge-app-peach.vercel.app\" style=\"color:var(--accent);text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.05em\">FORGE</a></footer>\n\n<script>\n    pdfjsLib.GlobalWorkerOptions.workerSrc = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/3.11.174/pdf.worker.min.js';\n    let pdfDoc = null, pages = [], currentFile = null;\n\n    const dropzone = document.getElementById('dropzone');\n    const fileInput = document.getElementById('fileInput');\n    const grid = document.getElementById('grid');\n    const controls = document.getElementById('controls');\n    const loader = document.getElementById('loader');\n\n    // Force reliable event handling\n    const triggerUpload = () => fileInput.click();\n    dropzone.addEventListener('click', triggerUpload);\n    dropzone.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); triggerUpload(); });\n    \n    dropzone.addEventListener('dragover', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); dropzone.style.borderColor = 'var(--accent)'; });\n    dropzone.addEventListener('dragleave', () => { dropzone.style.borderColor = 'var(--border)'; });\n    dropzone.addEventListener('drop', (e) => { \n        e.preventDefault(); \n        dropzone.style.borderColor = 'var(--border)';\n        handleFiles(e.dataTransfer.files); \n    });\n    \n    fileInput.addEventListener('change', (e) => handleFiles(e.target.files));\n\n    async function handleFiles(files) {\n        if (!files || files.length === 0) return;\n        currentFile = files[0];\n        loader.classList.remove('hidden');\n        \n        try {\n            const arrayBuffer = await currentFile.arrayBuffer();\n            pdfDoc = await pdfjsLib.getDocument({data: arrayBuffer}).promise;\n            pages = [];\n            grid.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            for (let i = 1; i <= pdfDoc.numPages; i++) {\n                const page = await pdfDoc.getPage(i);\n                const viewport = page.getViewport({ scale: 0.5 });\n                const canvas = document.createElement('canvas');\n                const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\n                canvas.height = viewport.height;\n                canvas.width = viewport.width;\n                await page.render({ canvasContext: ctx, viewport }).promise;\n                \n                const pageObj = { pageNumber: i, dataUrl: canvas.toDataURL(), selected: false };\n                pages.push(pageObj);\n                \n                const card = document.createElement('div');\n                card.className = 'card';\n                card.innerHTML = `<img src=\"${pageObj.dataUrl}\"><p>Page ${i}</p>`;\n                card.addEventListener('click', () => { \n                    pageObj.selected = !pageObj.selected; \n                    card.classList.toggle('selected'); \n                    updateUI(); \n                });\n                grid.appendChild(card);\n            }\n            dropzone.classList.add('hidden');\n            controls.style.display = 'flex';\n            updateUI();\n        } catch (e) { \n            console.error(e);\n            alert(\"Error reading PDF: \" + e.message); \n        }\n        loader.classList.add('hidden');\n    }\n\n    function updateUI() {\n        const count = pages.filter(p => p.selected).length;\n        document.getElementById('pageCount').innerText = `${count} selected`;\n        document.getElementById('downloadBtn').disabled = count === 0;\n    }\n\n    function toggleSelection(type) {\n        pages.forEach((p, i) => {\n            if (type === 'all') p.selected = true;\n            else if (type === 'none') p.selected = false;\n            else if (type === 'invert') p.selected = !p.selected;\n            grid.children[i].className = `card ${p.selected ? 'selected' : ''}`;\n        });\n        updateUI();\n    }\n\n    function applyRange() {\n        const val = document.getElementById('rangeInput').value;\n        if(!val) return;\n        const ranges = val.split(',');\n        pages.forEach(p => p.selected = false);\n        \n        ranges.forEach(r => {\n            const range = r.trim();\n            if (range.includes('-')) {\n                const [start, end] = range.split('-').map(Number);\n                for (let i = start; i <= end; i++) if (pages[i-1]) pages[i-1].selected = true;\n            } else {\n                const idx = Number(range);\n                if (pages[idx-1]) pages[idx-1].selected = true;\n            }\n        });\n        pages.forEach((p, i) => grid.children[i].className = `card ${p.selected ? 'selected' : ''}`);\n        updateUI();\n    }\n\n    async function processDownload() {\n        if(!currentFile) return;\n        loader.classList.remove('hidden');\n        try {\n            const newPdf = await PDFLib.PDFDocument.create();\n            const existingPdf = await PDFLib.PDFDocument.load(await currentFile.arrayBuffer());\n            const selectedPages = pages.filter(p => p.selected).map(p => p.pageNumber - 1);\n            const copiedPages = await newPdf.copyPages(existingPdf, selectedPages);\n            copiedPages.forEach(p => newPdf.addPage(p));\n            \n            const bytes = await newPdf.save();\n            const blob = new Blob([bytes], { type: 'application/pdf' });\n            const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n            const a = document.createElement('a');\n            a.href = url;\n            a.download = `Split_${currentFile.name}`;\n            a.click();\n        } catch (e) { \n            console.error(e);\n            alert(\"Export failed: \" + e.message); \n        }\n        loader.classList.add('hidden');\n    }\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>",
  "mode": "build",
  "toolName": "A pdf splitter tool with previews and ev",
